WEBVTT

00:04.538 --> 00:09.241
The history of Irish cops
in New York goes back 150 years.

00:09.243 --> 00:11.287
The statue we're dedicating

00:11.288 --> 00:13.796
commemorates the Irish-American
immigration history

00:13.797 --> 00:17.733
as told through 150 years
of Irish men and women

00:17.736 --> 00:19.302
serving across the ranks

00:19.304 --> 00:21.270
of the NYPD.

00:21.272 --> 00:22.872
And up the ranks.

00:22.874 --> 00:26.075
Thank you for that,
Madam President.

00:26.077 --> 00:27.210
MAN:
And because that history

00:27.212 --> 00:28.911
is also tied
to the DA's office,

00:28.913 --> 00:30.046
uh, we'd welcome

00:30.048 --> 00:32.982
your representatives
at the ceremony itself.

00:32.984 --> 00:34.684
While the district attorney
could not attend today,

00:34.686 --> 00:36.919
he's assured me that he will
be attending the ceremony.

00:36.921 --> 00:38.354
For clearance purposes,

00:38.356 --> 00:40.723
we'll need a rundown
of the attendees from your side

00:40.725 --> 00:41.991
who will be at the unveiling.

00:41.993 --> 00:44.027
Fair enough. I'll get that
to you this afternoon.

00:44.029 --> 00:48.131
Well, President Sullivan,
Chief Farrelly,

00:48.133 --> 00:49.699
it's a lovely gesture.

00:49.701 --> 00:51.134
Gonna be a great day.

00:51.136 --> 00:52.635
Thank you.

00:56.307 --> 00:57.640
Lovely to meet you, Erin.

00:57.642 --> 00:59.909
It's nice to meet you.
I'll see you at the ceremony.

00:59.911 --> 01:01.477
You bet.

01:05.183 --> 01:07.850
FRANK: And how long are you
going to be in New York?

01:09.621 --> 01:10.920
Erin.

01:10.922 --> 01:12.755
Chief Farrelly.

01:12.757 --> 01:14.190
Uh, I have a favor.

01:15.093 --> 01:16.959
My father was murdered here

01:16.961 --> 01:19.295
in New York City back in 1974.

01:19.297 --> 01:21.431
I'm so sorry.

01:21.433 --> 01:23.299
Now, we immediately moved back
to Ireland after that,

01:23.301 --> 01:25.568
but I was just wondering

01:25.570 --> 01:28.204
any chance you could give me
what you have on his case?

01:28.206 --> 01:30.073
Sure, I'll look into it for you.

01:32.243 --> 01:33.342
Thanks.

01:33.344 --> 01:35.778
Sure.

01:35.780 --> 01:37.714
SULLIVAN: ... and then
heading to Washington

01:37.716 --> 01:39.382
where I'm meeting
with the president

01:39.384 --> 01:40.883
Friday afternoon.

01:40.885 --> 01:42.485
Oh, well, anything
I can do to help

01:42.487 --> 01:44.120
before you head down
to Washington,

01:44.122 --> 01:45.354
please don't hesitate.

01:45.356 --> 01:47.056
GARRETT: Excuse me,
Madam President,

01:47.058 --> 01:50.193
I need the commissioner,
if you'll excuse us.

01:50.195 --> 01:51.394
Sorry.
Mm.

01:51.396 --> 01:54.097
Again, thanks.

01:57.102 --> 01:59.335
We just got a call from
the Nassau County Commissioner.

01:59.337 --> 02:01.704
The FBI is in Little Neck Bay

02:01.706 --> 02:03.372
conducting
a homicide investigation.

02:03.374 --> 02:06.476
Word is there may be
multiple victims dumped there.

02:06.478 --> 02:08.978
(sighs)
And?

02:08.979 --> 02:10.012
The initial forensics point

02:10.014 --> 02:12.849
to our serial killer,
Thomas Wilder.

02:15.553 --> 02:17.053
(sighs)

02:24.529 --> 02:25.962
Hey, do you believe
in soul mates?

02:25.964 --> 02:27.864
What do you mean?

02:27.866 --> 02:30.266
The notion that...

02:30.268 --> 02:33.703
there's only
one person for everyone.

02:33.705 --> 02:35.271
Yeah, I guess so, why?

02:35.273 --> 02:37.173
Because I read an article
that said that statistically

02:37.175 --> 02:39.642
there's only
one-and-a-half-billion chance

02:39.644 --> 02:41.811
that you'll ever actually
meet that person.

02:41.813 --> 02:43.146
I think you're over thinking it.

02:43.148 --> 02:44.914
DISPATCH:
15 Edward, be advised

02:44.916 --> 02:47.116
we have a white male
armed with a machete

02:47.118 --> 02:49.485
at 512 East End Avenue.

02:49.487 --> 02:51.754
There is a woman slashed
at that location.

02:51.756 --> 02:53.022
Any units on the back?

02:53.024 --> 02:55.091
Central, this is 12 David.
We're on the back.

02:55.093 --> 02:56.759
(siren wails)

02:56.761 --> 02:58.361
Sir, you don't want to do this!

02:58.363 --> 03:00.096
Stand back!
(overlapping shouting)

03:00.098 --> 03:01.664
Drop the knife, sir.

03:01.666 --> 03:02.665
Get back!
Get the hell back!

03:02.667 --> 03:04.133
(panting):
Drop the knife!

03:04.135 --> 03:05.334
No, take it easy, all right?

03:05.336 --> 03:07.170
Take it easy!
Drop it!

03:07.172 --> 03:08.237
Right there, stop!

03:08.239 --> 03:09.172
(sobs)

03:09.174 --> 03:10.773
(sirens chirp)

03:10.775 --> 03:12.575
Get up. Get up. Come on.

03:12.577 --> 03:14.310
Get back as far
as you can.

03:14.312 --> 03:15.812
(indistinct shouting)

03:15.814 --> 03:16.913
Hey, take it easy.
Why don't you just tell us

03:16.915 --> 03:18.114
what's up here, buddy.

03:18.116 --> 03:19.849
She took my kid, man.
She's trying to take my kid.

03:19.851 --> 03:21.584
That's my son!
WOMAN: You'll never see him again!

03:21.586 --> 03:22.385
(sobbing)

03:22.387 --> 03:23.386
Get her out of here!
Shut up!

03:23.388 --> 03:24.854
Hey, no one's doing
anything right now.

03:24.856 --> 03:26.389
You hear me?
No one's doing anything.

03:26.391 --> 03:27.857
All right?
You hear me?

03:29.460 --> 03:30.960
(panting)

03:30.962 --> 03:33.529
I got this.
Everyone just back up.

03:33.531 --> 03:35.398
JANKO: Let's give
him some space.

03:35.400 --> 03:36.499
Let's step back, let's go.

03:36.501 --> 03:37.600
Hey.
Everyone get back.

03:37.602 --> 03:38.668
Get back.
Don't look at them.

03:38.670 --> 03:40.603
Look at me.

03:40.605 --> 03:44.774
You don't drop it right now,
this isn't gonna end well, okay?

03:44.776 --> 03:46.209
Everyone's scared here,
everyone's jumpy.

03:46.211 --> 03:48.144
You don't put
the knife down right now,

03:48.146 --> 03:49.679
I'm afraid
what's gonna happen to you.

03:49.681 --> 03:51.514
(crying):
She took my kids, man.

03:51.516 --> 03:52.748
JAMIE:
Okay.

03:52.750 --> 03:54.283
She took my son.

03:54.285 --> 03:55.651
I hear you, but she's not dead.

03:55.653 --> 03:57.286
You didn't kill anyone.
Eddie, asp.

03:57.288 --> 03:58.928
We don't want to hurt you,
you understand?

04:00.091 --> 04:01.157
We don't want to kill you.

04:01.159 --> 04:02.592
(crying):
She took my kid, I don't know.

04:02.594 --> 04:04.794
JAMIE: I'm your friend here,
I'm being your friend here.

04:04.796 --> 04:06.128
I don't know.
I'm listening.

04:06.130 --> 04:07.430
(grunts)
(screams)

04:07.432 --> 04:10.099
(grunting)

04:10.101 --> 04:11.601
(loud grunt)

04:13.271 --> 04:15.271
(Jaime panting)

04:15.273 --> 04:17.206
You all right?
(panting): Oh, yeah.

04:17.208 --> 04:19.608
You're okay.

04:19.611 --> 04:22.545
(panting)
All right.

04:22.547 --> 04:27.116
(distant sirens,
indistinct radio chatter)

04:28.019 --> 04:30.086
Hey, you can't go in there.

04:30.088 --> 04:31.120
The hell I can't.

04:31.122 --> 04:32.488
NYPD.

04:32.490 --> 04:34.557
AGENT: Nassau County,
it's not your place.

04:34.559 --> 04:36.592
Yeah, but it's my case.

04:36.594 --> 04:37.960
You're Danny Reagan.

04:37.962 --> 04:39.095
Who the hell are you?

04:39.097 --> 04:41.697
Adam Parker,
FBI behavioral analyst.

04:41.699 --> 04:43.165
Oh, you're a
behavioral analyst?

04:43.167 --> 04:45.902
Okay, well then you should
realize that I'm pissed off.

04:45.904 --> 04:48.304
Why the hell didn't you tell me
you found another body?

04:48.306 --> 04:49.372
We're not sure

04:49.374 --> 04:50.439
if it involves him yet.

04:50.441 --> 04:52.041
But you did find another body.
Yes.

04:52.043 --> 04:53.242
You can say that.

